71  #define BASE_ELEM_DEF9(elem, id, lparen, args, rparen, symtype, class, symclass, dynamic) \
72  elem = NULL; \
73  ref_ptr<const Token> id_ptr = id; \
74  ref_ptr<const Token> lparen_ptr = lparen; \
75  ref_ptr<TermList> args_ptr = args; \
76  ref_ptr<const Token> rparen_ptr = rparen; \
77  size_t arity = (args_ptr ? args_ptr->size() : 0); \
78  \
79  /* Check to see if we have constants in any of the terms */ \
80  bool good = true; \
81  if (!parser->lang()->support(Language::Feature::FORMULA_CONSTANT_ARGS) && arity) { \
82  int cargs = 0; \
83  /*BOOST_FOREACH(Element const* elem, *args_ptr) { */ \
84  for (TermList::const_iterator it = args_ptr->begin(); it != args_ptr->end(); it++) { \
85  cargs |=(*it)->cmask(); \
86  } \
87  if (cargs) { \
88  parser->_feature_error(Language::Feature::FORMULA_CONSTANT_ARGS, &id->beginLoc()); \
89  good = false; \
90  } \
91  } \
92  \
93  if (good) { \
94  Symbol const* sym = parser->symtab()->resolve(symtype, *id_ptr->str(), arity); \
95  \
96  if (!sym && dynamic) { \
97  /* Dynamic declarations are allowed. Attempt to create a new symbol */ \
98  ref_ptr<ConstantSymbol::SortList> sorts = new ConstantSymbol::SortList(); \
99  int argnum = 0; \
100  if (args) { \
101  BOOST_FOREACH(Term const* t, *args_ptr) { \
102  argnum++; \
103  switch (t->subType()) { \
104  case Term::Type::VARIABLE: \
105  sorts->push_back(((Variable const*)t)->symbol()->sort()); \
106  break; \
107  case Term::Type::CONSTANT: \
108  sorts->push_back(((Constant const*)t)->symbol()->sort()); \
109  break; \
110  case Term::Type::ANON_VAR: \
111  case Term::Type::NULLARY: \
112  case Term::Type::LUA: \
113  case Term::Type::OBJECT: \
114  case Term::Type::BINARY: \
115  case Term::Type::UNARY: \
116  case Term::Type::BINDING: \
117  parser->_parse_error("Unable to dynamically declare abAction \"" + Symbol::genName(*id_ptr->str(), (args_ptr ? args_ptr->size() : 0))\
118  + "\". Could not deduce the sort of argument #" + boost::lexical_cast<std::string>(argnum) \
119  + " as it isn't a constant or variable. This problem can be fixed by explicitly declaring the abAction" \
120  " prior to this rule.", &id_ptr->beginLoc()); \
121  good = false; \
122  break; \
123  } \
124  } \
125  } \
126  if (good) { \
127  ref_ptr<ConstantSymbol> cs = new ConstantSymbol(ConstantSymbol::Type::ABACTION, id_ptr->str(), parser->symtab()->bsort(SymbolTable::BuiltinSort::BOOLEAN), sorts);\
128  /* add the sort to the symbol table */ \
129  if (!parser->symtab()->create(cs)) { \
130  /* It seems there was a problem. */ \
131  parser->_parse_error("An error occurred while declaring \"" + Symbol::genName(*id_ptr->str(), (args_ptr ? args_ptr->size() : 0)) + "\".");\
132  good = false; \
133  break; \
134  } else sym = cs; \
135  } \
136  } \
137  \
138  if (!good) { \
139  YYERROR; \
140  } else if (!sym || sym->type() != symtype) { \
141  /* The preprocessor indicated this was a constant and it's not... oops. */ \
142  parser->_parse_error(std::string("INTERNAL ERROR: Could not locate symbol table entry for ") \
143  + Symbol::Type::cstr(symtype) + " \"" + Symbol::genName(*id_ptr->str(), arity) \
144  + "\".", &id_ptr->beginLoc()); \
145  YYERROR; \
146  } else { \
147  elem = new class((symclass*)sym, args, id_ptr->beginLoc(), (arity ? rparen_ptr->endLoc() : id_ptr->endLoc())); \
148  } \
149  } \
150 
151  #define BASE_ELEM_BARE_DEF(elem, id, symtype, class, symclass) \
152  elem = NULL; \
153  ref_ptr<const Token> id_ptr = id; \
154  \
155  Symbol const* sym = parser->symtab()->resolve(symtype, *id_ptr->str()); \
156  if (sym && sym->type() == symtype) { \

162  + "\".", &id_ptr->beginLoc()); \
163  YYERROR; \

286  #define ATOMIC_FORMULA(af, constant, value) \
287  af = NULL; \
288  ref_ptr<Constant> c_ptr = constant; \
289  \
290  \
291  ref_ptr<const ObjectSymbol> t = \
292  (value ? parser->symtab()->bobj(SymbolTable::BuiltinObject::TRUE) \
293  : parser->symtab()->bobj(SymbolTable::BuiltinObject::FALSE)); \
294  \
295  \

563 /* The next thing included is series of defines which control
564 ** various aspects of the generated parser.
565 ** YYCODETYPE is the data type used for storing terminal
566 ** and nonterminal numbers. "unsigned char" is
567 ** used if there are fewer than 250 terminals
568 ** and nonterminals. "int" is used otherwise.
569 ** YYNOCODE is a number of type YYCODETYPE which corresponds
570 ** to no legal terminal or nonterminal number. This
571 ** number is used to fill in empty slots of the hash
572 ** table.
573 ** YYFALLBACK If defined, this indicates that one or more tokens
574 ** have fall-back values which should be used if the
575 ** original value of the token will not parse.
576 ** YYACTIONTYPE is the data type used for storing terminal
577 ** and nonterminal numbers. "unsigned char" is
578 ** used if there are fewer than 250 rules and
579 ** states combined. "int" is used otherwise.
580 ** lemon_parserTOKENTYPE is the data type used for minor tokens given
581 ** directly to the parser from the tokenizer.
582 ** YYMINORTYPE is the data type used for all minor tokens.
583 ** This is typically a union of many types, one of
584 ** which is lemon_parserTOKENTYPE. The entry in the union
585 ** for base tokens is called "yy0".
586 ** YYSTACKDEPTH is the maximum depth of the parser's stack. If
587 ** zero the stack is dynamically sized using realloc()
588 ** lemon_parserARG_SDECL A static variable declaration for the %extra_argument
589 ** lemon_parserARG_PDECL A parameter declaration for the %extra_argument
590 ** lemon_parserARG_STORE Code to store %extra_argument into yypParser
591 ** lemon_parserARG_FETCH Code to extract %extra_argument from yypParser
592 ** YYNSTATE the combined number of states.
593 ** YYNRULE the number of rules in the grammar
594 ** YYERRORSYMBOL is the code number of the error symbol. If not
595 ** defined, then do no error processing.
596 */

683 /* Next are the tables used to determine what action to take based on the
684 ** current state and lookahead token. These tables are used to implement
685 ** functions that take a state number and lookahead value and return an
686 ** action integer.
687 **
688 ** Suppose the action integer is N. Then the action is determined as
689 ** follows
690 **
691 ** 0 <= N < YYNSTATE Shift N. That is, push the lookahead
692 ** token onto the stack and goto state N.
693 **
694 ** YYNSTATE <= N < YYNSTATE+YYNRULE Reduce by rule N-YYNSTATE.
695 **
696 ** N == YYNSTATE+YYNRULE A syntax error has occurred.
697 **
698 ** N == YYNSTATE+YYNRULE+1 The parser accepts its input.
699 **
700 ** N == YYNSTATE+YYNRULE+2 No such action. Denotes unused
701 ** slots in the yy_action[] table.
702 **
703 ** The action table is constructed as a single large table named yy_action[].
704 ** Given state S and lookahead X, the action is computed as
705 **
706 ** yy_action[ yy_shift_ofst[S] + X ]
707 **
708 ** If the index value yy_shift_ofst[S]+X is out of range or if the value
709 ** yy_lookahead[yy_shift_ofst[S]+X] is not equal to X or if yy_shift_ofst[S]
710 ** is equal to YY_SHIFT_USE_DFLT, it means that the action is not in the table
711 ** and that yy_default[S] should be used instead.
712 **
713 ** The formula above is for computing the action when the lookahead is
714 ** a terminal symbol. If the lookahead is a non-terminal (as occurs after
715 ** a reduce action) then the yy_reduce_ofst[] array is used in place of
716 ** the yy_shift_ofst[] array and YY_REDUCE_USE_DFLT is used in place of
717 ** YY_SHIFT_USE_DFLT.
718 **
719 ** The following are the tables generated in this section:
720 **
721 ** yy_action[] A single table containing all actions.
722 ** yy_lookahead[] A table containing the lookahead for each entry in
723 ** yy_action. Used to detect hash collisions.
724 ** yy_shift_ofst[] For each state, the offset into yy_action for
725 ** shifting terminals.
726 ** yy_reduce_ofst[] For each state, the offset into yy_action for
727 ** shifting non-terminals after a reduce.
728 ** yy_default[] Default action for each state.
729 */
730 #define YY_ACTTAB_COUNT (3485)

1625 **
1626 ** %fallback ID X Y Z.
1627 **

1629 ** and Z. Whenever one of the tokens X, Y, or Z is input to the parser
1630 ** but it does not parse, the type of the token is changed to ID and
1631 ** the parse is retried before an error is thrown.

1701  0, /* BRACKET_L => nothing */
1702  0, /* BRACKET_R => nothing */
1703  0, /* COLON_DASH => nothing */
1704  0, /* CBRACKET_L => nothing */
1705  0, /* CBRACKET_R => nothing */
1706  0, /* PAREN_L => nothing */
1707  0, /* PAREN_R => nothing */
1708  0, /* PERIOD => nothing */
1709  0, /* MACRO_STRING => nothing */
1710  0, /* TILDE => nothing */
1711  0, /* DBL_COLON => nothing */
1712  0, /* ARROW_LEQ => nothing */
1713  0, /* ARROW_REQ => nothing */
1714  0, /* ARROW_LDASH => nothing */
1715  0, /* COLON => nothing */
1716  0, /* EQ => nothing */
1717  0, /* DBL_EQ => nothing */
1718  0, /* NEQ => nothing */
1719  0, /* NOT_EQ => nothing */
1720  0, /* LTHAN => nothing */
1721  0, /* GTHAN => nothing */
1722  0, /* LTHAN_EQ => nothing */
1723  0, /* GTHAN_EQ => nothing */
1724  0, /* DBL_PERIOD => nothing */
1725  0, /* BIG_CONJ => nothing */
1726  0, /* BIG_DISJ => nothing */
1727  0, /* POUND => nothing */
1728  0, /* SEMICOLON => nothing */
1729  0, /* EQUIV => nothing */
1730  0, /* IMPL => nothing */
1731  0, /* ARROW_RDASH => nothing */
1732  0, /* DBL_PLUS => nothing */
1733  0, /* PIPE => nothing */
1734  0, /* DBL_GTHAN => nothing */
1735  0, /* DBL_LTHAN => nothing */
1736  0, /* AMP => nothing */
1737  0, /* COMMA => nothing */
1738  0, /* DBL_AMP => nothing */
1739  0, /* NOT => nothing */
1740  0, /* DASH => nothing */
1741  0, /* PLUS => nothing */
1742  0, /* STAR => nothing */
1743  0, /* INT_DIV => nothing */
1744  0, /* MOD => nothing */
1745  0, /* ABS => nothing */
1746  0, /* CARROT => nothing */
1747  0, /* UMINUS => nothing */
1748  0, /* PREC_4 => nothing */
1749  0, /* PREC_3 => nothing */
1750  0, /* PREC_2 => nothing */
1751  0, /* PREC_1 => nothing */
1752  0, /* PREC_0 => nothing */
1753  0, /* EOF => nothing */
1754  0, /* ERR_IO => nothing */
1755  0, /* ERR_UNKNOWN_SYMBOL => nothing */
1756  0, /* ERR_UNTERMINATED_STRING => nothing */
1757  0, /* ERR_UNTERMINATED_ASP => nothing */
1758  0, /* ERR_UNTERMINATED_LUA => nothing */
1759  0, /* ERR_UNTERMINATED_F2LP => nothing */
1760  0, /* ERR_UNTERMINATED_BLK_COMMENT => nothing */
1761  0, /* ERR_SYNTAX => nothing */
1762  0, /* ERR_PAREN_MISMATCH => nothing */
1763  0, /* ARG => nothing */
1764  0, /* NOOP => nothing */
1765  2, /* CONSTANT_ID => IDENTIFIER */
1766  2, /* VARIABLE_ID => IDENTIFIER */
1767  2, /* OBJECT_ID => IDENTIFIER */
1768 };
1769 #endif /* YYFALLBACK */
1770 
1771 /* The following structure represents a single element of the
1772 ** parser's stack. Information stored includes:
1773 **
1774 ** + The state number for the parser at this level of the stack.
1775 **
1776 ** + The value of the token stored at this level of the stack.
1777 ** (In other words, the "major" token.)
1778 **
1779 ** + The semantic value stored at this level of the stack. This is
1780 ** the information used by the action routines in the grammar.
1781 ** It is sometimes called the "minor" token.
1782 */
1783 struct yyStackEntry {
1784  YYACTIONTYPE stateno; /* The state-number */
1785  YYCODETYPE major; /* The major token value. This is the code
1786  ** number for the token at this stack level */
1787  YYMINORTYPE minor; /* The user-supplied minor token value. This
1788  ** is the value of the token */
1789 };
1790 typedef struct yyStackEntry yyStackEntry;
1791 
1792 /* The state of the parser is completely contained in an instance of
1793 ** the following structure */
1794 struct yyParser {
1795  int yyidx; /* Index of top element in stack */
1796 #ifdef YYTRACKMAXSTACKDEPTH
1797  int yyidxMax; /* Maximum value of yyidx */
1798 #endif
1799  int yyerrcnt; /* Shifts left before out of the error */
1800  lemon_parserARG_SDECL /* A place to hold %extra_argument */
1801 #if YYSTACKDEPTH<=0
1802  int yystksz; /* Current side of the stack */
1803  yyStackEntry *yystack; /* The parser's stack */
1804 #else
1805  yyStackEntry yystack[YYSTACKDEPTH]; /* The parser's stack */
1806 #endif
1807 
1808  int yylookmajor; /* major token type for the lookahead token */
1809  YYMINORTYPE yylookminor; /* minor token type for the lookahead token */
1810  int yysyntaxerr; /* a flag used to trigger a syntax error */
1811 
1812 };
1813 typedef struct yyParser yyParser;
1814 
1815 #ifndef NDEBUG
1816 #include <stdio.h>
1817 static FILE *yyTraceFILE = 0;
1818 static char const*yyTracePrompt = 0;
1819 #endif /* NDEBUG */
1820 
1821 #ifndef NDEBUG
1822 /*
1823 ** Turn parser tracing on by giving a stream to which to write the trace
1824 ** and a prompt to preface each trace message. Tracing is turned off
1825 ** by making either argument NULL
1826 **
1827 ** Inputs:
1828 ** <ul>
1829 ** <li> A FILE* to which trace output should be written.
1830 ** If NULL, then tracing is turned off.
1831 ** <li> A prefix string written at the beginning of every
1832 ** line of trace output. If NULL, then tracing is
1833 ** turned off.
1834 ** </ul>
1835 **
1836 ** Outputs:
1837 ** None.
1838 */
1839 void lemon_parserTrace(FILE *TraceFILE, char const*zTracePrompt){
1840  yyTraceFILE = TraceFILE;
1841  yyTracePrompt = zTracePrompt;
1842  if( yyTraceFILE==0 ) yyTracePrompt = 0;
1843  else if( yyTracePrompt==0 ) yyTraceFILE = 0;
1844 }
1845 #endif /* NDEBUG */

2383 #if YYSTACKDEPTH<=0
2384 /*
2385 ** Try to increase the size of the parser stack.
2386 */
2387 static void yyGrowStack(yyParser *p){
2388  int newSize;
2389  yyStackEntry *pNew;
2390 
2391  newSize = p->yystksz*2 + 100;
2392  pNew = realloc(p->yystack, newSize*sizeof(pNew[0]));
2393  if( pNew ){
2394  p->yystack = pNew;
2395  p->yystksz = newSize;
2396 #ifndef NDEBUG
2397  if( yyTraceFILE ){
2398  fprintf(yyTraceFILE,"%sStack grows to %d entries!\n",
2399  yyTracePrompt, p->yystksz);
2400  }
2401 #endif
2402  }
2403 }
2404 #endif
2405 
2406 /*
2407 ** This function allocates a new parser.
2408 ** The only argument is a pointer to a function which works like
2409 ** malloc.
2410 **
2411 ** Inputs:
2412 ** A pointer to the function used to allocate memory.
2413 **
2414 ** Outputs:
2415 ** A pointer to a parser. This pointer is used in subsequent calls
2416 ** to lemon_parser and lemon_parserFree.
2417 */
2418 void *lemon_parserAlloc(void *(*mallocProc)(size_t)){
2419  yyParser *pParser;
2420  pParser = (yyParser*)(*mallocProc)( (size_t)sizeof(yyParser) );
2421  if( pParser ){
2422  pParser->yyidx = -1;
2423 #ifdef YYTRACKMAXSTACKDEPTH
2424  pParser->yyidxMax = 0;
2425 #endif
2426 #if YYSTACKDEPTH<=0
2427  pParser->yystack = NULL;
2428  pParser->yystksz = 0;
2429  yyGrowStack(pParser);
2430 #endif
2431  pParser->yylookmajor = YYNOCODE;
2432  pParser->yylookminor = yyzerominor;
2433  pParser->yysyntaxerr = 0;
2434  }
2435  return pParser;
2436 }
2437 
2438 /* The following function deletes the value associated with a
2439 ** symbol. The symbol can be either a terminal or nonterminal.
2440 ** "yymajor" is the symbol code, and "yypminor" is a pointer to
2441 ** the value.
2442 */
2443 static void yy_destructor(
2444  yyParser *yypParser, /* The parser */
2445  YYCODETYPE yymajor, /* Type code for object to destroy */
2446  YYMINORTYPE *yypminor /* The object to be destroyed */
2447 ){
2448  lemon_parserARG_FETCH;
2449  switch( yymajor ){
2450  /* Here is inserted the actions which take place when a
2451  ** terminal or non-terminal is destroyed. This can happen
2452  ** when the symbol is popped from the stack during a
2453  ** reduce or during error processing or when a parser is
2454  ** being destroyed before it is finished parsing.
2455  **
2456  ** Note: during a reduce, the only symbols destroyed are those
2457  ** which appear on the RHS of the rule, but which are not used
2458  ** inside the C code.
2459  */
2460  /* TERMINAL Destructor */
2461  case 1: /* INTEGER */
2462  case 2: /* IDENTIFIER */
2463  case 3: /* POUND_IDENTIFIER */
2464  case 4: /* POUND_INTEGER */
2465  case 5: /* AT_IDENTIFIER */
2466  case 6: /* STRING_LITERAL */
2467  case 7: /* ASP_GR */
2468  case 8: /* ASP_CP */
2469  case 9: /* LUA_GR */
2470  case 10: /* LUA_CP */
2471  case 11: /* F2LP_GR */
2472  case 12: /* F2LP_CP */
2473  case 13: /* COMMENT */
2474  case 14: /* CONSTANTS */
2475  case 15: /* INCLUDE */
2476  case 16: /* MACROS */
2477  case 17: /* OBJECTS */
2478  case 18: /* QUERY */
2479  case 19: /* SHOW */
2480  case 20: /* SORTS */
2481  case 21: /* VARIABLES */
2482  case 22: /* ABACTION */
2483  case 23: /* ACTION */
2484  case 24: /* ADDITIVEACTION */
2485  case 25: /* ADDITIVEFLUENT */
2486  case 26: /* AFTER */
2487  case 27: /* ALL */

3017 
3018 /*
3019 ** Pop the parser's stack once.
3020 **
3021 ** If there is a destructor routine associated with the token which
3022 ** is popped from the stack, then call it.
3023 **
3024 ** Return the major token number for the symbol popped.
3025 */
3026 static int yy_pop_parser_stack(yyParser *pParser){
3027  YYCODETYPE yymajor;
3028  yyStackEntry *yytos = &pParser->yystack[pParser->yyidx];
3029 
3030  if( pParser->yyidx<0 ) return 0;
3031 #ifndef NDEBUG
3032  if( yyTraceFILE && pParser->yyidx>=0 ){
3033  fprintf(yyTraceFILE,"%sPopping %s\n",
3034  yyTracePrompt,
3035  yyTokenName[yytos->major]);
3036  }
3037 #endif
3038  yymajor = yytos->major;
3039  yy_destructor(pParser, yymajor, &yytos->minor);
3040  pParser->yyidx--;
3041  return yymajor;
3042 }
3043 
3044 /*
3045 ** Deallocate and destroy a parser. Destructors are all called for
3046 ** all stack elements before shutting the parser down.
3047 **
3048 ** Inputs:
3049 ** <ul>
3050 ** <li> A pointer to the parser. This should be a pointer
3051 ** obtained from lemon_parserAlloc.
3052 ** <li> A pointer to a function used to reclaim memory obtained
3053 ** from malloc.
3054 ** </ul>
3055 */
3056 void lemon_parserFree(
3057  void *p, /* The parser to be deleted */
3058  void (*freeProc)(void*) /* Function used to reclaim memory */
3059 ){
3060  yyParser *pParser = (yyParser*)p;
3061  if( pParser==0 ) return;
3062  if( pParser->yylookmajor != YYNOCODE ) yy_destructor(pParser, (YYCODETYPE)pParser->yylookmajor, &pParser->yylookminor);
3063  while( pParser->yyidx>=0 ) yy_pop_parser_stack(pParser);
3064 #if YYSTACKDEPTH<=0
3065  free(pParser->yystack);
3066 #endif
3067  (*freeProc)((void*)pParser);
3068 }
3069 
3070 /*
3071 ** Return the peak depth of the stack for a parser.
3072 */
3073 #ifdef YYTRACKMAXSTACKDEPTH
3074 int lemon_parserStackPeak(void *p){
3075  yyParser *pParser = (yyParser*)p;
3076  return pParser->yyidxMax;
3077 }
3078 #endif
3079 
3080 /*
3081 ** Find the appropriate action for a parser given the terminal
3082 ** look-ahead token iLookAhead.
3083 **
3084 ** If the look-ahead token is YYNOCODE, then check to see if the action is
3085 ** independent of the look-ahead. If it is, return the action, otherwise
3086 ** return YY_NO_ACTION.
3087 */
3088 static int yy_find_shift_action(
3089  yyParser *pParser, /* The parser */
3090  YYCODETYPE iLookAhead /* The look-ahead token */
3091 ){
3092  int i;
3093  int stateno = pParser->yystack[pParser->yyidx].stateno;
3094 
3095  if( stateno>YY_SHIFT_COUNT
3096  || (i = yy_shift_ofst[stateno])==YY_SHIFT_USE_DFLT ){
3097  return yy_default[stateno];
3098  }
3099  assert( iLookAhead!=YYNOCODE );
3100  i += iLookAhead;
3101  if( i<0 || i>=YY_ACTTAB_COUNT || yy_lookahead[i]!=iLookAhead ){
3102  if( iLookAhead>0 ){
3103 #ifdef YYFALLBACK
3104  YYCODETYPE iFallback; /* Fallback token */
3105  if( iLookAhead<sizeof(yyFallback)/sizeof(yyFallback[0])
3106  && (iFallback = yyFallback[iLookAhead])!=0 ){
3107 #ifndef NDEBUG
3108  if( yyTraceFILE ){
3109  fprintf(yyTraceFILE, "%sFALLBACK %s => %s\n",
3110  yyTracePrompt, yyTokenName[iLookAhead], yyTokenName[iFallback]);
3111  }
3112 #endif
3113  return yy_find_shift_action(pParser, iFallback);
3114  }
3115 #endif
3116 #ifdef YYWILDCARD
3117  {
3118  int j = i - iLookAhead + YYWILDCARD;
3119  if(
3120 #if YY_SHIFT_MIN+YYWILDCARD<0
3121  j>=0 &&
3122 #endif
3123 #if YY_SHIFT_MAX+YYWILDCARD>=YY_ACTTAB_COUNT
3124  j<YY_ACTTAB_COUNT &&
3125 #endif
3126  yy_lookahead[j]==YYWILDCARD
3127  ){
3128 #ifndef NDEBUG
3129  if( yyTraceFILE ){
3130  fprintf(yyTraceFILE, "%sWILDCARD %s => %s\n",
3131  yyTracePrompt, yyTokenName[iLookAhead], yyTokenName[YYWILDCARD]);
3132  }
3133 #endif /* NDEBUG */
3134  return yy_action[j];
3135  }
3136  }
3137 #endif /* YYWILDCARD */
3138  }
3139  return yy_default[stateno];
3140  }else{
3141  return yy_action[i];
3142  }
3143 }
3144 
3145 /*
3146 ** Find the appropriate action for a parser given the non-terminal
3147 ** look-ahead token iLookAhead.
3148 **
3149 ** If the look-ahead token is YYNOCODE, then check to see if the action is
3150 ** independent of the look-ahead. If it is, return the action, otherwise
3151 ** return YY_NO_ACTION.
3152 */
3153 static int yy_find_reduce_action(
3154  int stateno, /* Current state number */
3155  YYCODETYPE iLookAhead /* The look-ahead token */
3156 ){
3157  int i;
3158 #ifdef YYERRORSYMBOL
3159  if( stateno>YY_REDUCE_COUNT ){
3160  return yy_default[stateno];
3161  }
3162 #else
3163  assert( stateno<=YY_REDUCE_COUNT );
3164 #endif
3165  i = yy_reduce_ofst[stateno];
3166  assert( i!=YY_REDUCE_USE_DFLT );
3167  if (iLookAhead == YYNOCODE) return YY_NO_ACTION;
3168  assert( iLookAhead!=YYNOCODE );
3169  i += iLookAhead;
3170 #ifdef YYERRORSYMBOL
3171  if( i<0 || i>=YY_ACTTAB_COUNT || yy_lookahead[i]!=iLookAhead ){
3172  return yy_default[stateno];
3173  }
3174 #else
3175  assert( i>=0 && i<YY_ACTTAB_COUNT );
3176  assert( yy_lookahead[i]==iLookAhead );
3177 #endif
3178  return yy_action[i];
3179 }

3718 /*
3719 ** Perform a reduce action and the shift that must immediately
3720 ** follow the reduce.
3721 */
3722 static void yy_reduce(
3723  yyParser *yypParser, /* The parser */
3724  int yyruleno /* Number of the rule by which to reduce */
3725 ){

3734  if( yyTraceFILE && yyruleno>=0
3735  && yyruleno<(int)(sizeof(yyRuleName)/sizeof(yyRuleName[0])) ){
3736  fprintf(yyTraceFILE, "%sReduce [%s].\n", yyTracePrompt,
3737  yyRuleName[yyruleno]);
3738  }
3739 #endif /* NDEBUG */
3740 
3741  /* Silence complaints from purify about yygotominor being uninitialized
3742  ** in some cases when it is copied into the stack after the following
3743  ** switch. yygotominor is uninitialized when a rule reduces that does
3744  ** not set the value of its left-hand side nonterminal. Leaving the
3745  ** value of the nonterminal uninitialized is utterly harmless as long
3746  ** as the value is never used. So really the only thing this code
3747  ** accomplishes is to quieten purify.
3748  **
3749  ** 2007-01-16: The wireshark project (www.wireshark.org) reports that
3750  ** without this code, their parser segfaults. I'm not sure what there
3751  ** parser is doing to make this happen. This is the second bug report
3752  ** from wireshark this week. Clearly they are stressing Lemon in ways
3753  ** that it has not been previously stressed... (SQLite ticket #2172)
3754  */
3755  /*memset(&yygotominor, 0, sizeof(yygotominor));*/
3756  yygotominor = yyzerominor;
3757 
3758  switch( yyruleno ){
3759  /* Beginning here are the reduction cases. A typical example
3760  ** follows:
3761  ** case 0:
3762  ** #line <lineno> <grammarfile>
3763  ** { ... } // User supplied code
3764  ** #line <lineno> <thisfile>
3765  ** break;
3766  */
3767  case 0: /* start ::= statement_lst EOF */
3768 #line 215 "bcplus/parser/detail/lemon_parser.y"
3769 {
3770  yy_destructor(yypParser,118,&yymsp[0].minor);
3771 }
3772 #line 3773 "bcplus/parser/detail/lemon_parser.c"
3773  break;
3774  case 3: /* statement_lst ::= statement_lst statement */
3775 #line 220 "bcplus/parser/detail/lemon_parser.y"
3776 {
3777  ref_ptr<Statement> ptr = yymsp[0].minor.yy10;
3778  yymsp[0].minor.yy10 = NULL;
3779  parser->_handle_stmt(ptr);
3780  }
3781 #line 3782 "bcplus/parser/detail/lemon_parser.c"
3782  break;
3783  case 4: /* statement ::= stmt_macro_def */
3784 #line 263 "bcplus/parser/detail/lemon_parser.y"
3785 { yygotominor.yy10 = yymsp[0].minor.yy291; }
3786 #line 3787 "bcplus/parser/detail/lemon_parser.c"

6320 /*
6321 ** Handles a syntax error within the parser.
6322 */
6323 static void yy_handle_err(yyParser* yypParser, int* yyerrorhit) {
6324  int yyact;
6325 #ifdef YYERRORSYMBOL
6326  int yymx;
6327 #endif
6328 #ifndef NDEBUG
6329  if( yyTraceFILE ){
6330  fprintf(yyTraceFILE,"%sSyntax Error!\n",yyTracePrompt);
6331  }
6332 #endif
6333 #ifdef YYERRORSYMBOL
6334  /* A syntax error has occurred.
6335  ** The response to an error depends upon whether or not the
6336  ** grammar defines an error token "ERROR".
6337  **
6338  ** This is what we do if the grammar does define ERROR:
6339  **
6340  ** * Call the %syntax_error function.
6341  **
6342  ** * Begin popping the stack until we enter a state where
6343  ** it is legal to shift the error symbol, then shift
6344  ** the error symbol.
6345  **
6346  ** * Set the error count to three.
6347  **
6348  ** * Begin accepting and shifting new tokens. No new error
6349  ** processing will occur until three tokens have been
6350  ** shifted successfully.
6351  **
6352  */
6353  yyact = YY_ERROR_ACTION;
6354  if( yypParser->yyerrcnt<0 ){
6355  yy_syntax_error(yypParser,yypParser->yylookmajor,yypParser->yylookminor);
6356  }
6357  yymx = yypParser->yystack[yypParser->yyidx].major;
6358  if( yymx==YYERRORSYMBOL || *yyerrorhit ){
6359 #ifndef NDEBUG
6360  if( yyTraceFILE ){
6361  fprintf(yyTraceFILE,"%sDiscard input token %s\n",
6362  yyTracePrompt,yyTokenName[yypParser->yylookmajor]);
6363  }
6364 #endif
6365  yy_destructor(yypParser, (YYCODETYPE)yypParser->yylookmajor,&yypParser->yylookminor);
6366  yypParser->yylookmajor = YYNOCODE;
6367  yypParser->yylookminor = yyzerominor;
6368  }else{
6369  while(
6370  yypParser->yyidx >= 0 &&
6371  yymx != YYERRORSYMBOL &&
6372  (yyact = yy_find_reduce_action(
6373  yypParser->yystack[yypParser->yyidx].stateno,
6374  YYERRORSYMBOL)) >= YYNSTATE
6375  ){
6376  yy_pop_parser_stack(yypParser);
6377  }
6378  if( yypParser->yyidx < 0 || yypParser->yylookmajor==0 ){
6379  yy_destructor(yypParser,(YYCODETYPE)yypParser->yylookmajor,&yypParser->yylookminor);
6380  yy_parse_failed(yypParser);
6381  yypParser->yylookmajor = YYNOCODE;
6382  yypParser->yylookminor = yyzerominor;
6383  }else if( yymx!=YYERRORSYMBOL ){
6384  YYMINORTYPE u2;
6385  u2.YYERRSYMDT = 0;
6386  yy_shift(yypParser,yyact,YYERRORSYMBOL,&u2);
6387  }
6388  }
6389  yypParser->yyerrcnt = 3;
6390  *yyerrorhit = 1;
6391 #elif defined(YYNOERRORRECOVERY)
6392  /* If the YYNOERRORRECOVERY macro is defined, then do not attempt to
6393  ** do any kind of error recovery. Instead, simply invoke the syntax
6394  ** error routine and continue going as if nothing had happened.
6395  **
6396  ** Applications can set this macro (for example inside %include) if
6397  ** they intend to abandon the parse upon the first syntax error seen.
6398  */
6399  yy_syntax_error(yypParser,yypParser->yylookmajor,yypParser->yylookminor);
6400  yy_destructor(yypParser,(YYCODETYPE)yypParser->yylookmajor,&yypParser->yylookminor);
6401  yypParser->yylookmajor = YYNOCODE;
6402  yypParser->yylookminor = yyzerominor;
6403 
6404 #else /* YYERRORSYMBOL is not defined */
6405  /* This is what we do if the grammar does not define ERROR:
6406  **
6407  ** * Report an error message, and throw away the input token.
6408  **
6409  ** * If the input token is $, then fail the parse.
6410  **
6411  ** As before, subsequent error messages are suppressed until
6412  ** three input tokens have been successfully shifted.
6413  */
6414  if( yypParser->yyerrcnt<=0 ){
6415  yy_syntax_error(yypParser,yypParser->yylookmajor,yypParser->yylookminor);
6416  }
6417  yypParser->yyerrcnt = 3;
6418  yy_destructor(yypParser,(YYCODETYPE)yypParser->yylookmajor,&yypParser->yylookminor);
6419  if( yyendofinput ){
6420  yy_parse_failed(yypParser);
6421  }
6422  yypParser->yylookmajor = YYNOCODE;
6423  yypParser->yylookminor = yyzerominor;
6424 #endif
6425  yypParser->yysyntaxerr = 0;
6426 }
6427

6429 /*
6430 ** Prepares the parser to accept tokens injected at the current
6431 ** location by extracting the lookahead token so that it can be
6432 ** reintroduced into the stream.
6433 ** Also pops the latest symbol off the parser's stack if the pop
6434 ** option is asserted.
6435 **
6436 ** returns the major type of the lookahead token that has been
6437 ** cleared from the parser or YYNOCODE and sets the lookahead minor
6438 ** type appropriately.
6439 */
6440 int lemon_parserPreInject(void* yyp, int pop, lemon_parserTOKENTYPE* lookahead) {
6441  yyParser* pParser = (yyParser*)yyp;
6442  int code = pParser->yylookmajor;
6443  if (pop && pParser->yyidx) yy_pop_parser_stack(pParser);
6444  if (code != YYNOCODE) {
6445  *lookahead = pParser->yylookminor.yy0;
6446  pParser->yylookmajor = YYNOCODE;
6447  pParser->yylookminor = yyzerominor;
6448  return code;
6449  } else {
6450  *lookahead = yyzerominor.yy0;
6451  return 0;
6452 
6453  }
6454 }

6471 /*
6472 ** Checks to see if there is a next-token independent reduction rule
6473 ** and executes it.
6474 */
6475 void lemon_parserAttemptReduce(void* yyp lemon_parserARG_PDECL) {
6476  yyParser* yypParser = (yyParser*)yyp;
6477  lemon_parserARG_STORE;
6478  int act = 0;
6479  int yyerrorhit = 0;
6480  do {
6481  yypParser->yysyntaxerr = 0;
6482  act = yy_find_reduce_action(yypParser->yystack[yypParser->yyidx].stateno, YYNOCODE);
6483  if (act >= YYNSTATE && act < YYNSTATE + YYNRULE) {
6484  // There is a reduce action. Do it.
6485  yy_reduce(yypParser, act-YYNSTATE);
6486  }
6487 
6488  if (yypParser->yysyntaxerr) {
6489  yy_handle_err(yypParser, &yyerrorhit);
6490  }
6491 
6492  } while (act >= YYNSTATE && act < YYNSTATE + YYNRULE);
6493 }

6495 /* The main parser program.
6496 ** The first argument is a pointer to a structure obtained from
6497 ** "lemon_parserAlloc" which describes the current state of the parser.
6498 ** The second argument is the major token number. The third is
6499 ** the minor token. The fourth optional argument is whatever the
6500 ** user wants (and specified in the grammar) and is available for
6501 ** use by the action routines.

6503 ** Inputs:
6504 ** <ul>
6505 ** <li> A pointer to the parser (an opaque structure.)
6506 ** <li> The major token number.
6507 ** <li> The minor token number.
6508 ** <li> An option argument of a grammar-specified type.
6509 ** </ul>
6510 **
6511 ** Outputs:
6512 ** None.
6513 */
6514 void lemon_parser(

6524

6526  yypParser = (yyParser*)yyp;
6527  if( yypParser->yyidx<0 ){
6528 #if YYSTACKDEPTH<=0

6533  yyStackOverflow(yypParser/*, &yyminorunion */);
6534  return;
6535  }
6536 #endif
6537  yypParser->yyidx = 0;
6538  yypParser->yyerrcnt = -1;
6539  yypParser->yystack[0].stateno = 0;
6540  yypParser->yystack[0].major = 0;

6542  yypParser->yylookmajor = yymajor;

6544  yyendofinput = (yypParser->yylookmajor==0);
6545  lemon_parserARG_STORE;
6546 
6547 #ifndef NDEBUG
6548  if( yyTraceFILE ){
6549  fprintf(yyTraceFILE,"%sInput %s\n",yyTracePrompt,yyTokenName[yypParser->yylookmajor]);
6550  }
6551 #endif

6555  if( yyact<YYNSTATE ){

6558  yypParser->yyerrcnt--;
6559  yypParser->yylookmajor = YYNOCODE;
6560  yypParser->yylookminor = yyzerominor;
6561  }else if( yyact < YYNSTATE + YYNRULE ) {

6563  } else {

6566  }

6570  }
6571  }while( yypParser->yylookmajor!=YYNOCODE && yypParser->yyidx>=0 );
